patrons__battle__territory:
* Philip V is recognised as King of Spain but renounces his place in the French succession
* Spain cedes the Spanish Netherlands, Naples, Milan and Sardinia to Austria, Sicily to Savoy, Gibraltar and Menorca to Great Britain
* France cedes Ypres to Austria while gaining the Principality of Orange and the Ubaye Valley
* Dutch Republic is awarded barrier fortresses

* The Habsburg monarchy wins lands in Ottoman Hungary, the Principality of Transylvania and the Balkans
* Poland-Lithuania captures Podolia.
* Russia captures the port of Azov.
* Venice captures Morea and inner Dalmatia.
* Montenegro gains de facto independence.
Treaty of Frederiksborg: Holstein–Gottorp loses its part of the Duchy of Schleswig to Denmark.
Treaties of Stockholm: Prussia gains parts of Swedish Pomerania; Hanover gains Bremen-Verden.
Treaty of the Pruth: Azov area is ceded back to the Ottoman Empire. Russia demolishes strategic castles such as Taganrog. Charles XII of Sweden gets safe passage from Turkey to Sweden in 1711.
Treaty of Nystad: Russia gains the three dominions Estonia, Livonia and Ingria as well as parts of Kexholm and Viborg.
